JO  - AMJ
SP  - 205
EP  - 214
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the extent to which the percentage of outside directors on a corporation?s board of directors, the concentration of equity ownership, and the roles of individual and institutional stockholders influence the company?s R&D strategy. We found that high insider representation on a board and a concentration of equity among institutional investors positively affected corporate R&D spending.
