TY  - JOUR
T1  - Communication with Employees Following a Merger: A Longitudinal Field Experiment
AU  - Schweiger, David M.
AU  - Denisi, Angelo S.
Y1  - 1991/03/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256304
DO  - 10.5465/256304
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 110
EP  - 135
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the impact of a realistic merger preview, a program of realistic communications, on employees of an organization that had just announced a merger. Employees in one plant received the preview and those in another received limited information. Results based on four collections of data indicated that the preview reduced dysfunctional outcomes of the merger. Those effects continued over the duration of the study and, in some cases, measured attributes returned to levels comparable to their levels before the merger was announced. We discuss implications for organizations contemplating mergers or acquisitions and for researchers interested in such activities.
AB  - This study examined the impact of a realistic merger preview, a program of realistic communications, on employees of an organization that had just announced a merger. Employees in one plant received the preview and those in another received limited information. Results based on four collections of data indicated that the preview reduced dysfunctional outcomes of the merger. Those effects continued over the duration of the study and, in some cases, measured attributes returned to levels comparable to their levels before the merger was announced. We discuss implications for organizations contemplating mergers or acquisitions and for researchers interested in such activities.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256304
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256304
